Adaeze had been staring at the same Solidity error for six hours when the gas fee finally cleared. Her tiny ERC-20 token — AGBO, named after her grandmother's market — was live on Base mainnet. She refreshed Basescan three times. 0x... confirmed. She screamed so loud her neighbor knocked on the wall. She didn't care. For the first time in her life, she owned something no government could freeze.
